headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 12 of his 30 points in the fourth quarter to help Chicago force overtime, and the Bulls then pulled away from the Indiana Pacers for a 120-112 victory Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls run past Pacers with late flurry for 120-112 OT win

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 37 points in an entertaining duel with ex-teammate John Wall, and the Wizards beat the undermanned Houston Rockets 131-119 on Monday night in Wall's return to Washington.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal outduels ex-teammate Wall, Wizards top Rockets 131-119

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored a season-high 44 points, making a career-best seven 3-pointers and leading the New York Knicks to their third straight victory, 123-112 over the slumping Atlanta Hawks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle scores 44 points, Knicks beat slumping Hawks 123-112

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson scored a season-high 40 points to power the streaking Utah Jazz past the Philadelphia 76ers 134-123 in a matchup of conference leaders Monday night despite a career-best 42 points from Ben Simmons.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson (40), streaking Jazz win showdown vs Simmons, 76ers

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 36 points in three quarters and the Golden State Warriors routed the Cleveland Cavaliers 129-98 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry nets 36, Warriors deal Cavs 8th straight loss, 129-98

headlines.description: — Marcus Morris had season highs of 32 points and six 3-pointers, and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Miami Heat 125-118 on Monday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morris comes up big in Clippers' 125-118 win over Heat

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored a season-high 40 points, James Harden had his fifth triple-double with Brooklyn and the Nets beat the Sacramento Kings 136-125 on Monday night as injured Kevin Durant watched from the bench.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving scores 40, Harden triple-double as Nets thump Kings
